narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The topics were more interesting than most of the other ROTC classes, and you'll learn a decent amount about how radar, sonar, and naval weapons work.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think it was about as good as could be hoped for, and LT Alfstad did well to make the class somewhat fun.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: You're gonna take it if you're a Navy option NROTC student, for other students you can take it if you're very interested in the technical workings of sonar, radar, and weapons systems that the navy employs. You don't get credit, though so just be aware of that.
